.\" termin.al-name: logout
.\" termin.al-usage: logout
.\" termin.al-summary: End the authenticated session.
.TH LOGOUT 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
logout \- End the authenticated session.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
logout
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Names the future session-ending entry point. Authentication is intentionally unavailable in the current public application.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ logout
.fi
.SH NOTES
The command currently returns a stable unavailable-feature diagnostic and does not alter session state.
.SH SEE ALSO
help(1), man(1)
